sentences: Fayçal Azizi (Arabic: فيصل عزيزي; born 26 February 1986 in Tetuan) is a Moroccan singer-songwriter.
He's known for his song "Werda ala Werda" in the 2006 film The Bitter Orange, his songs with the band K'lma, and his 2015 cover of the Judeo-Moroccan folk song "Hak A Mama."
